 loadCSS</li>\n<li>improvement: by default exclude <code>wp-content/cache</code> and <code>wp-content/uploads</code> from CSS optimization (Divi, Avada &amp; possibly others store page-specific CSS there)</li>\n<li>bugfix: stop double try/catch-blocks</li>\n<li>misc. bugfixes (see <a href="https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize/commits/master">GitHub commit log</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is (supposed to be) the last minor release of the 2.3 branch, <a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2018/02/18/introducing-zytzagoos-major-changes-for-autoptimize-2-4/">2.4 is a major change with some big under-the-hood and functional changes</a>. That new version has been in the works for some months already and if you&#8217;re up for it you can install by simply <a href="https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize/archive/beta.zip">downloading this zip-file from GitHub.</a> The GitHub version will also auto-update thanks to the great <a href="https://github.com/YahnisElsts/plugin-update-checker/">Plugin Update Checker</a> library.</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2012/11/06/dipping-below-the-magical-1-second-page-load-time/" rel="bookmark" title="Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time">Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time </a></li>\n<li><a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2015/12/09/bringing-autoptimize-2-0-beta-to-a-christmas-tree-near-you/" rel="bookmark" title="Bringing Autoptimize 2.0 (beta) to a Christmas-tree near you">Bringing Autoptimize 2.0 (beta) to a Christmas-tree near you </a></li>\n<li><a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2016/07/24/preparing-for-autoptimize-2-0-3-or-2-1-0/" rel="bookmark" title="Preparing (for) Autoptimize 2.0.3 or 2.1.0">Preparing (for) Autoptimize 2.0.3 or 2.1.0 </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_autoptimize/~4/3isMizv-2Qg" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explic